      "message": "Line 42: 🟡 Suggestion: `pushType.contains(\"audioCall\") || pushType.contains(\"videoCall\")` can classify unrelated push types as call notifications if those substrings appear anywhere in `pt`, which would still trigger wakelock, foreground-service startup, and `connectivityChanged(true)`. If `pt` has a constrained format, prefer exact matching or a parsed token check so only real call notifications take the expensive path.\n\n```suggestion\nval isCallNotification \u003d (pushType \u003d\u003d \"audioCall\" || pushType \u003d\u003d \"videoCall\")\n        \u0026\u0026 remoteMessage.originalPriority \u003d\u003d RemoteMessage.PRIORITY_HIGH\n```",
